name: intent
description:
The soil slipped from beneath my feet. I felt a pull.
In the bipolarity of my presence, existed a force within me.
Mocking, grounding, keeping themselves alive,
a parasite that couldn't exist without the very same soil.
Resisting now, as it realized that there was no ground.
Only a question, camouflaged in the abstraction of a choice.
